---
description: Standards for the Header and Content Modules
alwaysApply: false
---

- When a module starts with "Header", it is a header module
- When a module starts with "Content", "Cta", "Teaser" or something like that, it is a content module
- Graphql Fragments live inside the `src/datocms/data/modules` folder
- Graphql Fragments are named like the module (no "Fragment" suffix). E.g., for `ContentText`, the fragments name is `ContentText`.
- Graphql Types can be retrieved from `.astro/generated/datocms.types.ts`
- Module components are registerted in `src/config/modules.config.ts`
- Modules generally are added inside pages querys in `src/datocms/data/pagesGetPageBySlug.gql`. They may also be in other pages.

# Core Graphql Fragments and their types

- When a module fragment uses a LinkRecord, it should use the `src/datocms/data/core/Link.gql` fragment for it
- Other links that are **not** using the LinkRecord often use the `RecordLink` fragment

# Example for Header Module: Header Text

- Name: HeaderText
- Datocms Type, that is defined in @datocms.types.ts as HeaderTextRecord. It uses other types HeaderTextModelLeadField and LinkRecord
- Graphql Fragment
  - `src/datocms/data/modules/HeaderText.gql`
  - Used in `src/datocms/data/pagesGetPageBySlug.gql` in headerModule
- Component
  - `src/components/header-modules/HeaderText.astro`
  - Registered in `src/config/modules.config.ts`

# Example for Content Module: Content Text

- Name: ContentText
- Datocms Type, that is defined in @datocms.types.ts as ContentTextRecord. It uses another type ContentTextModelContentField
- Graphql Fragment
  - @ContentText.gql
  - Used in `src/datocms/data/pagesGetPageBySlug.gql` in contentModules
- Component
  - `src/components/content-modules/ContentText.astro`
  - Registered in `src/config/modules.config.ts`
